  "prompt": "Which best and cheap badminton racket should I buy?",
  "response": "When looking for a good yet affordable badminton racket, you'll want to consider factors such as weight, balance, and string tension. Here are a few recommendations that are known for their quality and affordability:\n\n1. **Yonex Nanoray Light 18i**:\n   - **Price Range**: Around $30 - $40\n   - **Key Features**: Lightweight (around 77 grams), head-light balance for quick maneuverability, suitable for beginners and intermediate players.\n\n2. **Li-Ning G-Force Superlite Carbon Fiber**:\n   - **Price Range**: Around $30 - $40\n   - **Key Features**: Carbon fiber construction, lightweight (around 78 grams), good for players looking for a balance between power and control.\n\n3. **Apacs Z Ziggler**:\n   - **Price Range**: Around $40 - $50\n   - **Key Features**: Lightweight (around 80 grams), even balance, suitable for players who want a versatile racket for both attacking and defensive play.\n\n4. **Victor Thruster K Hypernano**:\n   - **Price Range**: Around $50 - $60\n   - **Key Features**: Head-heavy balance for more powerful smashes, lightweight (around 82 grams), good for intermediate players looking to step up their game.\n\nThese rackets are generally well-reviewed and offer a great balance between cost and performance. If you're just starting out, the Yonex Nanoray Light 18i could be an excellent choice due to its ease of use and affordability.",
